        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 14 at 3:48PM CDT by NWS Jackson MS</headline>
        <description>At 348 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Crystal Springs, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Crystal Springs, Hazlehurst, Terry, Gallman, and Hopewell.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
